# Qualified-types tests excluded from -Ytest-pickler.
#
# The following four tests have qualifiers that reference the enclosing
# method (a self-recursive call inside the qualifier annotation), e.g.
# `def fib(n: Int): {res: Int with res == fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2)} = ...`.
# Unpickling the method's signature reads the annotation tree, which
# contains an `Apply(Ident(fib), ...)` whose type is computed via
# `tpd.Apply` -> `assignType` -> `fn.tpe.widen`, forcing `fib`'s info
# while it is still being read -> cyclic-reference assertion.
self_reference.scala
fib_selfify.scala
fib_memoized.scala
fib_memoized2.scala

# checked_array2 selects on an unstable receiver, which `asSeenFrom`
# skolemizes. `ENode.singleton` demotes that `SkolemType` to a fresh
# `ENodeVar.Skolem`, but the index isn't pickle-stable: the pre-pickle
# and post-unpickle traversals allocate from the per-owner counter in
# different states, so the printed indices diverge.
checked_array2.scala
